text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto R6Vx5W_threadScrollVars scroll-mb-[calc(var(--scroll-root-safe-area-inset-bottom,0px)+var(--thread-response-height))] scroll-mt-(--header-height)" dir="auto" data-turn-id="eace34a4-a308-42d5-a7db-e6126fd0f536" data-turn-id-container="eace34a4-a308-42d5-a7db-e6126fd0f536" data-testid="conversation-turn-1" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="user"><h4 class="sr-only select-none">You said:</h4><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto pt-3 [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div data-message-author-role="user" data-message-id="eace34a4-a308-42d5-a7db-e6126fd0f536" dir="auto" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden items-end rtl:items-start"><div class="flex flex-col w-fit max-w-(--user-chat-width,70%) items-start self-end rtl:items-end rtl:self-start"><div class="user-message-bubble-color corner-superellipse/0.98 relative min-w-0 overflow-hidden rounded-[22px] px-4 py-2.5 leading-6 w-full"><div data-custom-highlighting-behavior="boundary" class="A_HxFq_root" data-testid="collapsible-user-message-root"><input id="_r_2q_" aria-controls="_r_2p_" class="A_HxFq_toggleCheckbox" data-testid="collapsible-user-message-toggle-checkbox" type="checkbox"><div id="_r_2p_" data-testid="collapsible-user-message-content" class="A_HxFq_content"><div class="max-w-full min-w-0 [overflow-wrap:anywhere] whitespace-pre-wrap">salam, ai dersinden muelllim tapsiriq verib. imtahan suallarini verib ve onlari cavablandirib ona gondermemizi tapsirib, google doc faylinda. suallari sene atiram, her bir suali qisa ve aydin cavablandirib. google doc formatinda at.             1. Explain what is machine learning and what is artificial intelligence. Give 8 examples.
2. Explain with examples the terms supervised learning, unsupervised learning, and reinforcement learning.
3. Explain, with reference to concrete models, the terms overfitting and underfitting. How do we avoid these?
4. Explain with examples the terms parameter, hyper-parameter, and tuning.
5. Explain with examples: validation, cross-validation, training, and testing.
6. Describe with examples the main types of supervised learning problems.
7. What is a loss function? What role does it play in machine learning?
8. Give and explain two algorithms for finding a minimum of a loss function.
9. Compare the probabilistic approach to machine learning with the one based on minimising a loss function.
10. Explain the roles of calculus, linear algebra, and probability theory in machine learning.
11. Describe the functionality of the following libraries: numpy, pandas, tensorflow
12. Explain with an example what interpretability is, which machine learning models produce interpretable models, and which do not.
13. Suppose I want to model the salary of employees as a function of their educational background, experience, and other characteristics. Which models are appropriate, and why?
14. Suppose I want to model the species of an iris flower in terms of its physical measurements. Which models are appropriate, and why?
15. Suppose I want to write a program that recognises handwritten digits, given as a 32x32 grayscale image. How can I use machine learning to do this? 
16. What are GPUs, and why are they important in machine learning?



II: Classical models, part 1

17. Explain and compare the methods for converting a categorical variable into a numerical one. Why would we want to do this?
18. Explain linear regression. 
19. Explain polynomial regression.
20. Explain the k-nearest neighbours algorithm. 
21. Explain lasso regression and compare it with the plain linear regression.
22. Explain ridge regression and compare it with the plain linear regression.
23. Explain support vector machines.
24. Explain decision trees.
25. Explain logistic regression.
26. Suppose I can train binary (0-1) classifiers using some algorithm. What are the ways to learn to classify more than two categories using such binary classifiers?
27. With reference to concrete models, explain why we might want to scale variables in our dataset.
28. What are the ways to deal with missing data in our dataset?
29. Explain the terms accuracy and mean squared loss.
30. Which of the models for classification that we have seen produce linear decision boundaries, and which do not?
31. For three models of your choice, discuss how choosing the main hyper-paramater to be too large or too small can lead to overfitting or underfitting.
32. Explain Occam’s razor and its application to machine learning.</div></div><label for="_r_2q_" class="A_HxFq_toggleControl select-none" data-testid="collapsible-user-message-toggle"><span class="A_HxFq_showMoreLabel">Show more</span><span class="A_HxFq_showLessLabel">Show less</span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true" class="A_HxFq_toggleIcon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-6185c8f4.svg#ba3792" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></label></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex justify-end"><div aria-label="Your message actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto touch:opacity-100 duration-300 group-hover/turn-messages:delay-300 pointer-events-none opacity-0 motion-safe:transition-opacity group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:opacity-100 group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:opacity-100 has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:opacity-100" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy message" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-6185c8f4.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Share prompt" data-testid="share-prompt-link-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use hre