content" class="A_HxFq_content"><div class="max-w-full min-w-0 [overflow-wrap:anywhere] whitespace-pre-wrap">33. Compare decision trees with logistic regression. 
34. Compare decision tree regression with linear regression.
35. Choose three machine learning models, and compare their applicability to real-world problems.
36. Compare support vector machines with logistic regression.
37. Compare k-nearest neighbours with decision trees.
38. Explain what is feature selection, and give at least one way to do it.
39. Give three models that we have covered that, given sufficient data, can learn any relationship between the input and the output variables. Explain why not every model is universal in this sense. 
40. Discuss the parameters and hyper-parameters in the following: linear regression, k-nearest neighbours, and support vector machine without a kernel.
41. Discuss the parameters and hyper-parameters in the following: lasso regression, ridge regression, and support vector machine with the radial basis kernel
42.  Discuss the parameters and hyper-parameters in the following: decision tree, logistic regression, and k-nearest neighbours.
43. Choose three models for classification, and explain how they are trained.
44. Choose three models for regression, and explain how they are trained.
45. Explain the role of cross-validation. What are the possible alternatives to it?
46. Which models can be used both for classification and regression, and which cannot?
47. Suppose I have one independent variable X and one dependent variable Y, and the true relationship is Y = ax + b + N(0, 1), where N(0, 1) is a normally distributed error term with mean zero and variance one. Choose three different models, and explain whether they will be able to learn the true relationship if given a large amount of data.
48. What are learning curves? Given an example of how you might use them in the machine learning workflow.



IV: Neural networks

49. Explain how a neuron works.
50. What is a feedforward neural network, and what is a recurrent neural network?
51. What problems do neural networks solve?
52. Explain the inputs, outputs, and the loss function of a feedforward neural network for classification.
53. Explain how neural networks are trained.
54. Explain the terms: input layer, hidden layer, output layer, dense layer.
55. What are convolutional neural networks? Compare them to fully connected ones.
56. How many parameters and hyper-parameters does a neuron have? What is weight sharing in convolutional neural networks?
57. What is deep learning? What are its advantages and drawbacks?
58. Explain how a convolution layer works.
59. Explain how a pooling layer works, and why we use it.
60. Explain how linear regression and logistic regression can be captured by a neural network,
61. Compare the architectures of AlexNet and VGG; you do not need exact numbers of neurons and filters.
62. Suppose you work for a satellite company, and are asked to write a program that takes a square image, and decides whether it is part of a city, wilderness, or farmland. How would you solve this problem?
63. What are the parameters and hyper-parameters of neural networks?
64. Explain how batches, epochs, and randomness are used in training neural networks.


V: Beyond supervised learning

65. What are the problems of unsupervised learning? Give examples.
66. What is reinforcement learning?
67. Explain clustering and the k-means algorithmş
68. What is a search problem? Give examples of search algorithms.
69. What are expert systems? Give examples.
70. Give an example of a genetic algorithm. 
71. What is reward hacking in reinforcement learning? Give examples.
72. Explain breadth-first search in a graph. Give an example.
73. Explain depth-first search in a graph. Give an example.
74. What is A* search? Where can it be used?
75. Give examples of problems that can be solved using reinforcement learning.
76. What are the advantages and disadvantages of reinforcement learning compared to other approaches?
77. What is an autoencoder? Give an example.
78. What is dimensionality reduction? What methods for it are there? Give examples of problems where it is useful.
79. Give three examples of modern advances in AI.
80. Explain with an example what a generative model is, as opposed to a model that does classification or regression.        bunlarida cavabla </div></div><label for="_r_3t_" class="A_HxFq_toggleControl select-none" data-testid="collapsible-user-message-toggle"><span class="A_HxFq_showMoreLabel">Show more</span><span class="A_HxFq_showLessLabel">Show less</span><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true" class="A_HxFq_toggleIcon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-6185c8f4.svg#ba3792" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></label></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="z-0 flex justify-end"><div aria-label="Your message actions" class="touch:-me-2 touch:-ms-3.5 -ms-2.5 -me-1 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-y-4 p-1 select-none focus-within:transition-none hover:transition-none touch:pointer-events-auto touch:opacity-100 duration-300 group-hover/turn-messages:delay-300 pointer-events-none opacity-0 motion-safe:transition-opacity group-hover/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-hover/turn-messages:opacity-100 group-focus-within/turn-messages:pointer-events-auto group-focus-within/turn-messages:opacity-100 has-data-[state=open]:pointer-events-auto has-data-[state=open]:opacity-100" role="group" tabindex="-1" style="mask-position: 0% 0%;"><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Copy message" data-testid="copy-turn-action-button" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-6185c8f4.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></button><button class="text-token-text-secondary hover:bg-token-bg-secondary rounded-lg" aria-label="Edit message" data-state="closed"><span class="flex items-center justify-center touch:w-10 h-8 w-8"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="tr